    <section class="destination-section">
        <a class="anchor" id="montezuma-castle"></a>
        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Montezuma Castle National&nbsp;Monument</h2>
        <p>Approximately 40 minutes south of Sedona is a stunning pre-Colombian Native American cliff dwelling, called <strong>Montezuma Castle National Monument</strong>. The impressive structure only requires a short walk to admire and is highly recommended.</p>
        <h3>Montezuma Well</h3>
        <p>Nearby Montezuma Castle is <strong>Montezuma Well National Monument</strong>, a unique round lake surrounded by cliff dwellings built into the walls above the lake. The Montezuma Castle and Well are located along the route between Phoenix and Sedona.</p>
    </section>



